# Backend env template.
#
# This project uses two env files chosen at runtime by APP_ENV:
#   APP_ENV=dev  (default) → loads `.env.dev` — local Supabase
#   APP_ENV=prd            → loads `.env.prd` — hosted Supabase
#
# Setup:
#   cp .env.example .env.dev    # fill in local-Supabase values from `supabase status`
#   cp .env.example .env.prd    # fill in hosted-Supabase values from the dashboard
# Both files are gitignored.
#
# In production (Railway / Render / Fly), don't ship a .env file — set the
# variables in the platform's UI. BaseSettings reads process env vars first
# and falls back to the file, so the absence of the file is fine in prod.

# ---- Supabase ----
# .env.dev: `supabase status -o env` after `supabase start` (port 54321).
# .env.prd: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API + JWT Settings.
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY=
SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=

# Comma-separated list of frontend origins allowed to call this API.
# .env.dev: leave as the local Vite URLs.
# .env.prd: your deployed frontend (e.g. https://tracker.vercel.app).
CORS_ORIGINS=http://127.0.0.1:5173,http://localhost:5173

# Used in invitation emails / password-reset callbacks.
# .env.dev: http://localhost:5173
# .env.prd: https://tracker.vercel.app (your real frontend)
FRONTEND_URL=http://localhost:5173

# ---- Email (Resend) ----
# Transactional emails for urgent-task assignments. Use the same API key
# you set as the Supabase Auth custom SMTP password (Project Settings →
# Auth → SMTP). Username there is "resend"; the password is the API key.
# Leave RESEND_API_KEY empty in .env.dev to skip real sending (the email
# service logs the would-be send and returns).
RESEND_API_KEY=
# Sender shown in the recipient's inbox. Domain (thealanwang.xyz here)
# must already be verified in Resend — the default matches the Supabase
# Auth SMTP sender so it works out of the box without extra DNS.
EMAIL_SENDER=Tracker <noreply_tracker@thealanwang.xyz>

# ---- Stripe (billing) ----
# Optional — leave empty to disable billing (the /billing routes return 503).
# Use TEST-mode values while developing (free, fake cards). Get them from the
# Stripe Dashboard (Test mode):
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY     Developers → API keys → Secret key (sk_test_…)
#   STRIPE_PRO_PRICE_ID   the recurring "Trackly Pro" price (price_…). Must be an ACTIVE price
#                         in the same mode as the key — Checkout rejects archived prices, and a
#                         price-change in Stripe mints a NEW id, so update this when you re-price.
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET `stripe listen --forward-to localhost:8000/billing/webhook`
#                         prints whsec_… for local; in prod use the dashboard endpoint's secret.
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=
STRIPE_PRO_PRICE_ID=
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=

# ---- Anthropic (in-app AI agent) ----
# Optional — leave empty to disable the AI assistant (the /agent route
# returns 503 and the in-app panel shows a "not configured" state). Get a
# key from console.anthropic.com → API keys.
#   ANTHROPIC_API_KEY   sk-ant-…
#   AGENT_MODEL         override the default model (claude-sonnet-4-6).
#                       claude-haiku-4-5 is a cheaper option.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
AGENT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
